	the kind of property the General_property_definition defines.
Where applicable the following values shall be used:



'overall axle distance': The overall axle distance is the distance between the first front axle and the rear most axle of the vehicle combination;

'positioning': The General_property_definition is the definition of a  that provides a geometric model for a  or a  for the purpose of placement;


'theoretical wheelbase': The theoretical wheelbase is the distance between the resolved weight lines of front and rear axle combinations
For a single axle either in the front or at the rear, the resolved weight line is identical to the axle centre line.
				For a truck with one front axle and a combination of two rear axles, the theoretical axle distance is the distance between the front axle centre line and the resolved weight line of the rear axle combination. The resolved weight line is the calculated line, between two axles in a bogie, where the load from the axles is focused.
				If the load distribution between two rear axles is 60% vs. 40%, then the resolved weight line is placed 40% of the total distance between the axles, from the first rear axle towards the second rear axle.


'track': The track is the distance between the centre of the tyres mounted on an axle of a vehicle;


'wheel space': The wheel space is the distance between the perpendicular lines constructed to the longitudinal median plane of the vehicle from two points that represent the wheels situated at the same side of the axle that is of interest.

	the type of characteristic that is specified for an object.
The following values shall be used:


'centroid': The 'property_value' identifies the centre point of the mass of a body. The relative position of this point within the body is an invariant datum relative to rotation and translation.;
An example, where the use of this General_shape_dependent_property with property_type 'centroid' is used instead of the object , is the following: sometimes the General_shape_dependent_property is calculated by some system at some point of time. But there are cases where the information, e.g., the General_shape_dependent_property of a die, is transferred into a following stage, e.g., in order to perform a feasibility check, where there is only a simplified shape representation that does not allow to calculate the exact General_shape_dependent_property. Yet, in this stage the information about the General_shape_dependent_property is needed in order to check whether the transport of a die with a crane is feasible.


'surface area': The 'property_value' specifies the overall surface of the bodies contained in the referenced shape.;


'volume': The 'property_value' specifies the overall volume of the bodies contained in the referenced shape.

